rinetd-uv is a modernized implementation of the rinetd internet
redirection and load-balancing proxy server, rewritten to use the
libuv event loop library.

This program efficiently redirects (proxies) TCP and UDP connections
from one IP address/port combination to another. It is useful when
operating virtual servers, firewalls, and similar network infrastructure.

Key features:
- Event-driven I/O using libuv (high performance, low overhead)
- Both TCP and UDP support
- UNIX domain socket support
- IPv4 and IPv6 support
- Load balancing (round-robin, least-connections, random, IP-hash)
- Health checking with passive failure detection
- Allow/deny rules for access control
- Periodic DNS refresh for dynamic backend addresses
- YAML and classic rinetd.conf configuration formats
- Zero-copy buffer forwarding with configurable buffer pools

Maintains backward compatibility with the original rinetd configuration
format.

